In the no-pooling approach, it is only those three children from School X that contribute to the School X line. What would be great is if we could _somehow_ use the information from the other schools to inform our estimation of what is going on in School X. This is what multi-level modelling achieves, _partially_ pooling information across the groups, and this is where we'll turn to next.
